com.cerner.bunsen.mappings

Class ConceptMaps

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.cerner.bunsen.mappings.ConceptMaps

  • public class ConceptMaps
extends Object
    An immutable collection of FHIR ConceptMaps. This class is used to import concept map content, explore it, and persist it to a database.

      • getMaps

        public org.apache.spark.sql.Dataset<org.hl7.fhir.dstu3.model.ConceptMap> getMaps()
        Returns a dataset of concept maps to inspect metadata. Since the mappings themselves can be quite large, the maps in this dataset do not contain them. Instead, users should use the getMappings() method to query mappings in depth.
        Returns:
        a dataset of concept maps that do not containmappings.

      • writeToTables

        public void writeToTables(String mappingsTable,
                          String conceptMapTable,
                          String ancestorsTable)
        Writes mappings to the given tables.

        Warning: these updates are likely not atomic due to the lack of transactional semantics in the underlying data store. Concurrent users may see previous items removed before new ones are added, or items appear separately than others. This is intended for use in a user-specific sandbox or staging environment.

        Parameters:
        mappingsTable - name of the table containing the mapping records
        conceptMapTable - name of the table containing the concept map metadata
        ancestorsTable - name of the table containing transitive ancestors
